COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"## Pain Point\r\n\r\nCurrently, the I/O in these operations is purely file based, it would be better and also more in line with long term goals of the project to support streams as well.\r\n\r\n## Proposed Solution\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-stream.html#asyncio-tcp-echo-client-streams\r\n\r\n* For archives, if you go with streams\r\n    - Accept streams for the archive to unpack and the stream to pack data into.\r\n    - Use paths for directories to extract data into and pack data from.\r\n\r\nFor more information check the following links: \r\n* [Weekly-Sync-Tuesday-June-29th-2021 [45:44]](https://youtu.be/AM62czYTdDM?t=2743) \r\n* [Meeting Minutes [See `\"Tuesday June 29th 2021\" > \"Saahil\" > \"Operations for archives and compression\"`]](https://docs.google.com/document/d/16u9Tev3O0CcUDe2nfikHmrO3Xnd4ASJ45myFgQLpvzM/edit)","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intel/dffml/issues/1145/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intel/dffml/issues/1145/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}